FBIS4-23755 "drafr115_c_94008" FBIS-AFR-94-115 Daily Report 13 Jun 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA ANC Rejects Allegations of Blackmailing Zulu King ANC Rejects Allegations of Blackmailing Zulu King MB1306203594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1600 GMT 13 Jun 94 MB1306203594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] The ANC has rejected allegations that it wants to control the Zulu king. ANC spokesman Blade Nzimande said the organization was insisting that the king's status and remuneration be entrenched in the constitution. He accused the IFP [Inkatha Freedom Party] of blackmailing the king by paying his salary and of preventing him from establishing relations with those of his subjects who belong to other parties.
